    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Homework III: Indirect Connections and Matrices\"\n---\n\n\n\n\n## Undirected Paths\n\nConsider the graph shown in @fig-grex1:\n\n\n::: {.cell fig-cap-location='margin'}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![An undirected graph.](homework3-answered_files/figure-html/fig-grex1-1.png){#fig-grex1 width=1152}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Write down *all* the **paths** of length four ($l = 4$) connecting node *B* and node *E*:\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> B </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> C </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> A </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> F </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> E </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> B </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> C </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> A </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> J </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> E </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> B </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> C </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> I </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> F </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> E </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> B </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> K </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> D </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> J </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> E </td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Write down *all* the **paths** of length two ($l = 2$) featuring node *D* as the **inner node**:\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table>\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th style=\"text-align:left;\">  </th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GDH </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GDI </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GDJ </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GDK </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> GDL </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HDI </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HDJ </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HDK </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HDL </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> IDJ </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> IDK </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> IDL </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> JDK </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> JDL </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> KDL </td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n1. Write down *all* the **shortest paths** connecting nodes *A* and *D*:\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> A </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> J </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> D </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> A </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> I </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> D </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> A </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> H </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> D </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> A </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> G </td>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> D </td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Write down *all* the **cycles** of length *three* that start and end with node *H*:\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table>\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th style=\"text-align:left;\">  </th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HDGH </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HDIH </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HGAH </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HGIH </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HIAH </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HIFH </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> HAFH </td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n## Directed Paths\n\nConsider the graph shown in @fig-grex2:\n\n\n::: {.cell fig-cap-location='margin'}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![A directed graph.](homework3-answered_files/figure-html/fig-grex2-1.png){#fig-grex2 width=1536}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n1. Write down *all* the **directed path(s)** of *any* length going *from* node *F* *to* node *A*:\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table>\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th style=\"text-align:left;\"> Paths </th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> F, D, G, H, C, A </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> F, H, C, A </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td style=\"text-align:left;\"> F, J, H, C, A </td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n`````\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n1. What is the length of the **shortest directed path(s)** going *from* node *I* *to* node *H*?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n```\n[1] 3\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n1. If *B* wanted to send a message to *C* in the most efficient way, how many intermediaries would *B* have to use?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n```\n[1] 2\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Matrices\n\n- In the matrix below, write down the cell entries **geodesic distance matrix** corresponding to the graph shown in @fig-grex1:\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n`````{=html}\n<table class=\"table\" style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th style=\"text-align:left;\">   </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> A </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> B </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:center;\"> C </th>\n   <th style=\"text-align:cen